===Etymology===
Alteration of Middle English [[wyvere]], ''viper'', from Old North French [[wivre]], from Latin [[vipera]].
===Noun===
'''wyvern''' ([[wyverns]])

#(a) Mythical [[dragon]]-like creature, having wings, only two legs and a [[barb]]ed tail.

